node.text:
The Dolce&Gabbana Alta Sartoria collection arouses unique emotions as exquisite silks, brocades, velvets, glass and crystals, embroideries and precious fabrics come together in a perfect melody of beauty and Italian craftsmanship. 

Watch the #DGAltaSartoria show and discover more at the link in bio. 
 
#DGLovesVenice #DGFattoAMano #MadeInItaly #DolceGabbana

node.text:
Exploring our roots to create what's next: introducing #DGNextChapter, the Women's Fall Winter 21 Fashion Show.
 
In collaboration with @istitutoitalianoditecnologia, the #DGFW21 Collection reveals how technology and craftsmanship, two apparently different worlds, come together in a celebration of Fatto a Mano. The new looks, inspired by robotics research and Artificial Intelligence, also pay tribute to #DolceGabbana DNA of the ‘90s. 
 
Stay tuned for the Fashion Show on Monday, March 1st at 4PM CET.

node.text:
The next chapter of the #FollowYourGroove campaign features the new #DGNS1 Graffiti edition. The new #DGSneaker with a unique all-over pattern inspired by six of the world’s most vibrant cities: Milan, London, Paris, Miami, Los Angeles and New York City, each represented by local artists who represent the grooves of their city through unique creative content.

@reynanoriega_ is a Miami-based, Black and Afro-Latina visual artist, author and educator who chose to follow her groove by creating graphic design, paintings, digital illustrations and photography that could portray different figures of people of colour, architectural spaces and landscapes. Her main aim is to inspire women from different cultures and backgrounds to recognize themselves, feel represented, and empowered. 

Discover more at the link in bio.

#DolceGabbana

The next chapter of the #FollowYourGroove campaign features the new #DGNS1 Graffiti edition. The new #DGSneaker with a unique all-over pattern inspired by six of the world’s most vibrant cities: Milan, London, Paris, Miami, Los Angeles and New York City, each represented by local artists who represent the grooves of their city through unique creative content. 
 
@jasminsehra is from London and is a freelance illustrator and designer who chose to follow her groove by promoting art about identity, empowerment, self-love and positivity. She has worked with a diverse variety of clients by doing illustrative works of art. Her work has been awarded on various creative platforms including Vice, D&AD, HypeBeast, among others. 
 
Discover more at the link in bio. 
 
#DolceGabbana
